        Converts a uri to a serial string by replacing the head of it with a given prefix. Note that the result is not a uri. E.g.

        toSerialString(URI.create("https://my.org/foo/222)) would, assuming that https://my.org/foo is associated with the prefix "A" return

        A222

        The syntax of serial strings never varies: letters + digits, and the letters are just the prefix. This is how we isomorphically map uris to certificate serial strings.
